OL,6,FThe tribunal said: "In conclusion, the
OL,7,Ftribunal determined that Dr Aarella's
OL,8,Fconduct which he has now carried out
OL,9,Fagainst five junior colleagues, shows
OL,10,Fa reckless disregard for GMP and is
OL,11,Ffundamentally incompatible with
OL,12,Fcontinued registration."
OL,14,FThe tribunal was mindful that Dr
OL,15,FAarella has already been subject to a
OL,16,Fperiod of suspension, during which he
OL,17,Frepeated his behaviour and has not
OL,18,Fdemonstrated that he has been able to
OL,19,Fremediate this.
